Abstract

The subject of the proposal is to design economic AI agent that helps to make good economic decisions. Some people are lacking prior knowledge to choose the best economic option among the different options. The benefit of designing economic agent system to reduce the time of research among different options and financial cost. To decide which company is the highest profit, we need the stock price for each company then compare between them by using deep learning branch of machine learning that attempt to model high level abstraction in data. The important idea in designing stock AI agent is to increase prediction probability of profit or loss about previous studies. The interesting of the economic AI agent system it contains economic information to enable the customer to select the right direction. The result of comparison is to appearance most profit or loss, then order it from highest profit to loss.

Chapter One: Introduction

1.1Introduction

Artificial Intelligence is an extension for the computer science field, that deals machines, to find a solution for the problems that are hard to solve in the normal ways. AI includes taking characteristics from the human intelligence that is why it is called artificial intelligence, then it will be applied into the computers as algorithms. Depending on the sensitivity the requirements the approach will be either minor or vey extensive. In financial field, stocks are considered as a major tool for individuals in the several sectors. Most of the individuals who deal with stocks which you call them stockbrokers, use the fundamental and technical analysis or time series analysis or they use algorithms and theories such as neural networks, which are a powerful tool in predicating the stock prices in the market, or data mining and decision trees, which were designed to find the information needed and the patters and the requirements which the test data or the historical data can provide, to reach the decision of buying the stocks or not, but some experiments showed that some of these methods will produce un accurate results, form this point the need of new methods and ways for predicating the stock price came. To benefit the economic field, we decided to take advantage of AI and the machine learning algorithms in specific the deep learning approach and design an economic AI agent which is specialized in predicating the stock prices for a specific company.

As what we have said earlier, the problem that is stockbrokers in the financial market are often not sure from investing and purchasing stocks, because the data they have is incomplete or inaccurate, but now with the help of artificial intelligence, the stockbrokers are more confident and sure when buying stocks.

Stocks predication is considered to be a major issue in the financial field, which is the portion of ownership in corporation or company. The holder of a stock will have a portion of the companys earnings and will be affected with the risks and responsible for the portion of the company that each stock represents. In stocks filed, there are two main types or classes: common stock and In the stocks filed, the shareholder is any person, company or other institution that owns at least one share of a companys stock.

Our system will apply the deep learning approach which predicts the stock prices and will benefit the stockholders. Deep learning approach derives its behavior from the behavior the human brain when to making decisions and obtains knowledge from past experience or historical data or from a large set of data. This chapter will discuss problem definition, aims and objectives, timeline project, team qualification, conclusion and reference.

2

1.1.1 Deep learning implementation

Deep learning implementation to predict the stock price includes several steps which are data processing, model building, model operation, model evaluation and model optimization. First, the textual financial reports and stock data first are processed with some natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. For the price data, it need to be done with a price to label mapping. Financial indicators were computed to obtain a more complete analysis. For each stock, five machine learning models are used to train the models for comparisons, it should be trained for historical data to find the dependencies between input and output for more accurate prediction. The five models are SDA, DBN, modified RNN-RBN. SVM and RF. The first three are deep learning models, and the last two state-of- art and classic machine learning models. By optimizing the parameters, a relatively good model can be built. Then test data can be used to test the efficiency of the models. In the model operation step, some prediction scores can be obtained. The scores can map to the corresponding labels. At the phase of model evaluation, we can compare the models we build, and do some analysis. By the understanding of the models, we can return to the process of data processing, to change the methodology we used or optimized some parameters.

1.2Problem statement

Stock price prediction is one of the most widely studied and challenging problems which can decide the companies future, making different researchers from many fields including economics, history, finance, mathematics, and computer science to any attention and put effort into providing a solution to this above mention problem. Our brains are the best prediction machines which we have ever seen. Many people think of the brain as either a really powerful computer or just something too mysterious to explain. but when we judge something, we may make some errors, in addition to that stockbrokers and companies owners do not seem to have any intelligent tool that can help them advise clients on which stocks are suitable for any buy or sale trade. So, must depend on the AI economic agent to decide our decisions.

Chapter Two: Background

6

2.1Introduction

In the previous chapter we discussed the importance of predicating the stock price and how it effects the economic future of the companies, stock prices are considered to be very dynamic due to the several changes in the nature of the financial, any person in the economic would predict the stock price or purchase the stock before it rises again, or if the price rises, in this chapter we will highlight outline some of the theories, approaches and machine learning methods used in predicating the stock price in the market. This chapter will focus on the related work that could help us to improve our deep learning approach in predicting the stock price in the economic fields and stock markets.

2.1Background

Predicating and guessing the accurate value of the stock is one of the major problems in the economic world, many mathematical and machine earning learning solution have been developed in order to solve the mentioned problem, some of the researches mentioned some of the approaches that were used to solve the wrong prediction of the problem, but the results were dissatisfying.

Economics is considered to be a large field with a rich history that's been explored and examined by hundreds of influential people, ranging from philosophers to politician, it helps us to satisfy our endless needs and wants. [1]

As what we have said before, the prediction of stock prices has always been a very hard mission to accomplish, through several observations, it has been noticed that the stock price has nothing to do with the economic status of the company or the economic status of the country, in the present days the stock price is affected by many reasons such as political events, natural disasters. [2]

Technology and communication systems have been emerged very often, and due to this emerge the stock process to fluctuate very fast, and the stocks exchanges processes have been increased in a short time by stock brokers, banks and financial institutions.

2.2.1 Stock Markets

Stock markets can be very hard to predict. Depending on the supply and demand, macroeconomic changes such as inflation or political instability can affect the whole markets, while local events like company financial announcements or product releases impact individual stocks. All these factors must be considered by the investors and traders

7

when evaluating the stock, wither to continue with the purchase process or not. Market participants are often partitioned into two groups: Traders that make decisions based on news, facts and numbers are known as fundamental analysts, while those who look for signals in price history are using technical analysis. [3]

2.2.2 Stock Market Data

Stock market data is in several formats, from the information concerning each trade, what the data points contain may be different from one side to another, but a widely-used composition consists of six variables: Time, open, high, low, close and volume. Time is a reference to when the data point is from. Open and close is the share price at the beginning and end of the period, while high and low refers to the highest and lowest point the value reached throughout the period. Lastly, volume is the number of shares that were traded in total. [4]

2.2.3 Market Gaps

Market Gaps in stock exchanges allow certain participants to trade after closing hours. After-hours trades also important and impact the share value, but the price will not be reflected until the next day for the average trader.

2.2.4 Software of Deep Learning

Neural designed is a data mining tool, based on machine learning algorithm, deep learning is one them, is has a graphical user interface, which will make it easier for use to import data, the other system we found which are libraries most of them needs to be connected to an interface implemented using python or C++.

In Neural designer, we found tree types of recognition, pattern recognition, function recognition and time series recognition, in out project we will use either patter or time series recognition. Also using this software, we can design the model, in this part will import the data set, and the number of record in the data set will be calculated automatically and shown in the systems interface. There is a tasks part where we could use tasks to implement on our data, basic statistics is an example which will us to know the highest and lower price in our data for example. Also there is target distribution, in our project the target is whether to buy the stock or not. Deep agriculture is the part where we implement the deep learning approach, we will specify the number of hidden layers, which depends on the data we have.

In addition to that a training section which we will specify in the training criteria such as 8

how long it will take to train and the maximum iteration number and much more, and also when starting the training there is a part in the interface called engine it will show the output of the training which training the neural network. Then if the model training results is satisfactory no further training will be done and we will start testing the model and get the predictive values.

2.3Related Work

In this section, we will discuss some of the studies, which were involved in predicting the stock prices, many theories were found to help the inventors to predict whether to buy or invest in these stocks.

One of the first methods used in predicting the stock prices in the market was combining multiple feature selection methods for stock prediction which includes Union, intersection, and multi-intersection approaches, which identify more representative variables for better prediction [5], Eberhard used neural networks to predict stock prices, proved that neural networks can considerably improve the prognosis of stock prices and in more general way the prognosis of semi-chaotic time series in the future [6], Fung, Yu and Wai Lam predict the stock price by Integrating text mining approach using real-time news, previous studies showed that the relationship between news articles and stock prices do exist, but in their study were considering time series only using data mining. [7]

Schumaker used financial news to predict the stock prices, using textual representation and statistical machine learning methods on financial news. [8]

Echo state networks to predict stock prices created by Yixu Song, a novel recurrent neural network, echo state network (ESN) to predict the next closing price in stock markets. [9]

Neuro-genetic stock prediction system based on financial correlation between companies was presented by Yung-Keun Kwon 2005 a number of input variables are generated from the highly-correlated companies. [10]

Zhang and Akkaladev 2002 presented in their paper a granular neural web agent for stock prediction, it was developed using the granular neural network (GNN) that can discover fuzzy rules. Stock data sets are downloaded from www.yahoo.com, then datasets are inserted into the database tables using a java program. the GNN is trained using sample data for any stock, it learns about the history of the stock data and from there it can predict the future price. [11]

Empirical Analysis of optimal hidden neurons in neural network modeling for stock

prediction was produced by Jinchuan 2008, it is a new procedure in nonlinear interpolation 9

and demonstrates a potential of stock market prediction using incomplete, imprecise and noisy data. [12]

Artificial neural networks in the analysis and prediction of stock prices is another approach in predicating stock prices created by Fagner Andrade de Oliveira 2011 it utilizes artificial neural networks to predict the closing price of the stock Three stages were used to generate the prediction: obtainment of the samples, pre-processing, and prediction. [13]

Textual analysis of financial news articles, this research by Vatsal H. Shah 2007 which includes defining the news impact on a particular stock: Positive, Negative, and Neutral, news is considered to have a positive impact or negative impact if the stock price rises or drops significantly for a period. [14]

P.Y. Mok 2004 used the prediction algorithm is developed to improve stock index predictions using such extracted "news". linear regression model and nonlinear artificial neural network model are used to predict stock indexes of Open, Close, High and Low using the extracted news, and then they are compared with models using only raw intraday data. [15] Masoud Makrehchi 2013 used social media to extract significant stock movements and collect appropriate pre, post and contemporaneous text , and then it will train the model with this data [16].

K-Nearest Neighbor (kNN) Algorithm was used by Khalid Alkhatib 2013 to predict the stocks price, it was used because of its small error ratio, in addition, it depends on the actual stock prices data; the prediction results which was generated using the KNN method were close and almost parallel to actual stock prices. [17]

In 2009 stock temporal prediction based on time series motifs was created by Jun-Zhou Han 2009 which is an algorithm to discover self-correlation of stock price in virtue of the notion of time series motifs, using stock price sequences as time series. [18] A web based Fuzzy Neural networks for stock prediction was introduced by Fujun Xu and Yu Tang 2002, it is based on fuzzy neural network by using the past stock data to discover fuzzy rules and make future predictions. The learning algorithm is implemented input data to each network are the moving averages of the weekly stock data, the output simulation data are also the average values of the weekly stock data. [19]

Multiple programs and systems were found, that could predict the stock prices, stock- forecasting.com, is a well know site used to predict the companys stocks and generate stock predication in the next 5 days or 10 days, also a long term predication will be displayed as graphs. [20] Caffe is an open source deep learning framework made with expression, speed, and modularity used to build a classifier, but it doesnt include an interface, that is why it

10

needs to be build using C++ or Python .[21] Deep;earning4j is an open source library written in java programming language it includes implementations of the restricted Boltzmann machine , deep belief net, deep auto encoder.[22] The Microsoft Cognitive Toolkit, is a deep learning framework developed by Microsoft, it describes the neural network as a series of steps in the graph.[23] In our project we decided to use Neural Designer software, a data mining tool, based on machine learning algorithm, deep learning is one of them, is has a graphical user interface, which will make it easier for use to import data, like what you have said earlier, the other systems we found which are libraries most of them needs to be connected to an interface implemented using python or C++, having a built in interface give the neural network software a huge advantage, also Neural Designer software can work on input data set such as CSV and XLS files, also with database inputs such as MySQL and Oracle database.[24]

In addition to that, a data visualization feature is found to visualize reports in charts, tables and pictures, that will help uses to users to identify the structure of business data, which will make better and more informed business decisions. Neural designer is easy to use, has a user friendly interface and technically complete. Also it is good with processing large amount of data sets. Neural Designer is considered to be a model selection framework, which means the user can get a relevant variable in given process. Based on our research no disadvantage and drawback were found on Neural Designer software. In summery, its advanced neural network algorithms, combined with a simple user interface, which make Neural Designer the perfect tool which we can use to predict the stock prices.

2.4Summary

Stock prediction as what said before is a challenging issue facing the financial world these days, in order to develop or study a solutions to the problem, stock data and market gaps must be understood and clearly defined, many researches discussed or outlined solution to the problem associated with the stock predication issue, many of researchers used neural networks and designed a models to train the data they obtain in order to produce a informative data to predict the stock price, our intended methodology is develop an AI agent using deep learning approach which is considered to be much time efficient rather that the machine learning theories, using a smaller data set.

Chapter Three: Analysis and Methodology

14

3.1Introduction

One of the primary objectives of this project is to also provide financial analysts with a tool with which they can predict movements of stocks in a certain direction. The ability of the network to keep updating it with historical information will allow it to predict the data even more accurately and thus aim to increase the profitability for the investors and the users of this application. Some aspects that we aim at achieving is this regard are to aid the users of the software to make valuable decisions, help the investors to generate and maximize their profits out of the investments they make in the stock market, reduce the risk involved when investing in stocks and support the users in an efficient portfolio management.

In the previous chapter we discussed the importance of predicating the stock price and how it effects the economic future of the companies, also highlight outline some of the theories, approaches and machine learning methods used in predicating the stock price in the market. Analysis is a systematic examination and studying the nature of system and determining its essential feature and their relation. This chapter will focus on the details of form system and select the Functional and nonfunctional requirement.

3.2Scenario Description

Stock prices are considered to be very dynamic due to the several changes in the nature of the financial, any person in the economic would predict the stock price or purchase the stock before it rises again, or if the price rises, we design system enable the user enter to the web page and register your account by using your name and password, then display you all the stock of companies. And even make it easier for the users search process put in the top of page engine search to write name of company and then display stock raising and stock drop. In our Project will requires an input of some form of fundamental data, which comprises of the closing prices (of each day) of all the listed companies, with absolutely no fluctuations. The data which we used was from the website Stock Exchange, from the beginning of the year so far. Regarding the data with fluctuations, we will follow some techniques which give us an optimal solution dealing with the unsteady and varied flow. The data that we will get to us, either to be on the XML format, or .XLS format, where the data contains the names of companies, and the closing price of each company, and will be applying filters to become The data in the form of a uniform format.

15

Figure 1 This example for GSPC daily closing price development between Feb 28, 2016 and Feb 28, 2017

In order to have the right system good results, we need to achieve the following:

1. Authentication

In order to check the difference in the output data. we will many simulations were run in order to test the accuracy of the system.

2. Accuracy

To test the accuracy of the results we can use one of the methods of measuring the error rate, in our project we can use: MSE (Mean Square Error). On the assumption that a given computation scheme is stable, consideration of the accuracy of the scheme involves assessment of the correctness of the results yielded by the scheme.

3. Test Runs

Through this phase in order to check the reliability of our system as far as the predictions were concerned. In this part, after applying the calibration and verification processes, we looked at the outputs from the test runs.

3.3User Requirements

Functional Requirements describe a particular behavior of function of the system we certain condition are met. Nonfunctional Requirements describe how the system should behave and what limit there are on its functionality and specify the system quality attribute and characteristic.

16

3.3.1 Functional Requirements

4.6Algorithms

A Deep Learning consists of four main parts:

1.Processing units{uj}, where each uj has a certain activation level aj(t) at any point in time.

2.Weighted interconnections between the various processing units which determine how the activation of one unit leads to input for another unit.

3.An activation rule which acts on the set of input signals at a unit to produce a new output signal, or activation.

4.Optionally, a learning rule that specifies how to adjust the weights for a given input/output pair.

A processing unit uj takes a number of input signals, say a1j, a2j...,anj with corresponding weights w1j, w2j,...,wnj, respectively. The net input to uj given by:

netj = SUM (wij * aij)

The new state of activation of uj given by: aj(t+1) = F(aj(t),netj),

where F is the activation rule and aj(t) is the activation of uj at time t. The output signal oj of unit uj is a function of the new state of activation of uj:

oj(t+1) = fj(aj(t+1)).

One of the most important features of a Deep Learning is its ability to adapt to new environments. Therefore, learning algorithms are critical to the study of Deep Learnings.

4.9.2 Data Structures Description

Deep learning network is the best choice for this type of our application. In a deep learning, neurons are only connected forward. Each layer of the neural network contains connections to the next layer, but there are no connections back. Typically, the network consists of a set of sensory units (source nodes) that constitute the input layer, one or more hidden layers of computation nodes, and an output layer of computation nodes. In its common use, most neural networks will have one hidden layer, and it's very rare for a neural network to have more than two hidden layers. The input signal propagates through the network in a deep direction, on a layer by layer basis. These neural networks are commonly referred as deep learning perceptron's. Shown below is a simple deep learning with 4 inputs, 1 output, and 1 hidden layer.

using System;

using System.Collections.Generic; using System.Linq;

using System.Web;

///<summary>

///Summary description for ParserData

///</summary>

public class ParserData

{

public static List<Price> Parse(string csvData)

{

List<Price> prices = new List<Price>();

string[] rows = csvData.Replace("\r", "").Split('\n');

foreach (string row in rows)

{

if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(row)) continue;

string[] cols = row.Split(',');

Price p = new Price(); p.Date = cols[0]; p.Open = cols[1]; p.High = cols[2]; p.Low = cols[3]; p.Close = cols[4]; p.Volume = cols[5]; p.AdjClose = cols[6];

prices.Add(p);

}

return prices;

}

public class Price

{

public string Date { get; set; } public string Open { get; set; } public string High { get; set; } public string Low { get; set; } public string Close { get; set; } public string Volume { get; set; } public string AdjClose { get; set; } // public decimal Last { get; set; }

}

}

//#define LOG_DATASET using System;

using System.Text;

using System.Collections.Generic; using System.IO;

using System.Threading; using Encog.Neural.Networks;

using Encog.Neural.Networks.Layers; using Encog.Neural.Networks.Training; using Encog.Neural.Data.Basic;

using Encog.Neural.Networks.Training.LMA;

using Encog.Neural.Networks.Training.Propagation.Resilient; using Encog.Neural.Networks.Training.Anneal;

using Encog.Neural.Networks.Training.Strategy; using Encog.Neural.Activation;

using Encog.Persist.Persistors;

namespace FinancialMarketPredictor

{

/// Training algorithm

public enum TrainingAlgorithm

{

///Backpropagation learning Resilient,

///Simulated annealing Annealing,

///Evolutionary learning Evolutionary

}

///Training status delegate

///<param name="iteration">Epoch number</param>

///<param name="error">Error</param>

///<param name="algorithm">Training algorithm</param>

public delegate void TrainingStatus(int iteration, double error, TrainingAlgorithm algorithm);

/// Class for prediction

public sealed class PredictIndicators

{

private const int INDEXES_TO_CONSIDER = 1;

///Input Tuples. Each tuple consist of a pair: <c>Financial Data for comapany</c> index and prime interest rate PIR

///<remarks>

///The total amount of input synapses equals <c>InputTupples * IndexesToConsider</c>

///</remarks>

private const int INPUT_TUPLES = 10;

A.16

///The size of network's output private const int OUTPUT_SIZE = 1;

///Maximal error

private const double MAX_ERROR = 0.00005;

/// Network to be trained

private BasicNetwork p_network;

///Input data Financial Data for comapany private double[][] p_input;

///Desired output

private double[][] p_ideal;

/// Financial market predictor

private FinancialPredictorManager p_manager;

/// Training tread

private Thread p_trainThread;

///Path to Financial Data for comapany index CSV

//private string _pathtosp;

///Size of the training data

private int _trainingSize = 1000;

///Gets the information about the predictor public bool Loaded { get; private set; }

///Hidden layers

public int HiddenLayers { get; private set; }

/// Hidden units

public int HiddenUnits { get; private set; }

A.17

/// Maximum date for training and prediction

public DateTime MaxIndexDate

{

get

{

return p_manager == null ? DateTime.MinValue : p_manager.MaxDate;

}

}

 

/// Minimum date for training and prediction

 

public DateTime MinIndexDate

 

{

 

get

 

{

 

return p_manager == null ? DateTime.MaxValue : p_manager.MinDate;

 

}

 

}

 

/// Constructor for Prediction class

 

// Path to CSV with Financial Data for comapany index rates

 

//Number of hidden units per hidden layer

 

// Number of hidden layers

 

public PredictIndicators(string csvData, int hiddenUnits, int hiddenLayers)

 

{

 

if ( csvData ==null )

 

throw new ArgumentException("csvData targets an invalid file");

 

// _pathtosp = csvData;

 

CreateNetwork(hiddenUnits, hiddenLayers);

/*Create new

network*/

 

p_manager = new FinancialPredictorManager(INPUT_TUPLES, OUTPUT_SIZE); /*Create new financial predictor manager*/

p_manager.Load(csvData); /*Load Financial Data for comapany */

Loaded = true;

HiddenLayers = hiddenLayers; HiddenUnits = hiddenUnits;

}

///Reload indexes

///<param name="csvData">Financial Data for comapany date</param>

public void ReloadcsvData(string csvData)

{

if (csvData==null )

throw new ArgumentException("csvData targets an invalid data");

Loaded = false;

//_pathtosp = csvData;

A.18

p_manager = new FinancialPredictorManager(INPUT_TUPLES, OUTPUT_SIZE); /*Create new financial predictor manager*/

p_manager.Load(csvData); /*Load Financial Data for comapany*/ p_ideal = p_input = null;

Loaded = true;

}

/// Create a new network

private void CreateNetwork(int hiddenUnits, int hiddenLayers)

{

p_network = new BasicNetwork { Name = "Financial Predictor", Description = "Network for prediction analysis" };

p_network.AddLayer(new BasicLayer(INPUT_TUPLES * INDEXES_TO_CONSIDER)); /*Input*/

for (int i = 0; i < hiddenLayers; i++)

p_network.AddLayer(new BasicLayer(new ActivationTANH(), true, hiddenUnits)); /*Hidden layer*/

p_network.AddLayer(new BasicLayer(new ActivationTANH(), true, OUTPUT_SIZE));

/*Output of the network*/

 

p_network.Structure.FinalizeStructure();

/*Finalize network

structure*/

 

p_network.Reset();

/*Randomize*/

}

 

///Create Training sets for the neural network to be trained

///<param name="trainFrom">Initial date, from which to gather indexes</param>

///<param name="trainTo">Final date, to which to gather indexes</param> public void CreateTrainingSets(DateTime trainFrom, DateTime trainTo)

{

//find where we are starting from

int startIndex = -1; int endIndex = -1;

foreach (FinancialIndexes sample in p_manager.Samples)

{

if (sample.Date.CompareTo(trainFrom) < 0) startIndex++;

if (sample.Date.CompareTo(trainTo) < 0) endIndex++;

}

//create a sample factor across the training area _trainingSize = endIndex - startIndex; p_input = new double[_trainingSize][]; p_ideal = new double[_trainingSize][];

//grab the actual training data from that point for (int i = startIndex; i < endIndex; i++)

{

p_input[i - startIndex] = new double[INPUT_TUPLES * INDEXES_TO_CONSIDER]; p_ideal[i - startIndex] = new double[OUTPUT_SIZE]; p_manager.GetInputData(i, p_input[i - startIndex]); p_manager.GetOutputData(i, p_ideal[i - startIndex]);

}

using (StreamWriter writer = new StreamWriter("dataset.csv"), ideal = new StreamWriter("ideal.csv"))

{

for (int i = 0; i < p_input.Length; i++)

{

StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder();

A.19

for (int j = 0; j < p_input[0].Length; j++)

{

builder.Append(p_input[i][j]); if (j != p_input[0].Length - 1)

builder.Append(",");

}

writer.WriteLine(builder.ToString());

StringBuilder idealData = new StringBuilder(); for (int j = 0; j < p_ideal[0].Length; j++)

{

idealData.Append(p_ideal[i][j]); if (j != p_ideal[0].Length - 1)

idealData.Append(",");

}

ideal.WriteLine(idealData.ToString());

}

}

}

///Train the network using Backpropagation and SimulatedAnnealing methods

///<param name="trainTo">Train until a specific date</param>

///<param name="status">Callback function invoked on each _epoch</param>

///<param name="trainFrom">Initial date, from which to gather training data</param>

public void TrainNetworkAsync(DateTime trainFrom, DateTime trainTo, TrainingStatus status)

{

Action<DateTime, DateTime, TrainingStatus> action = TrainNetwork; action.BeginInvoke(trainFrom, trainTo, status, action.EndInvoke, action);

}

// Train network

///<param name="status">Delegate to be invoked</param>

///<param name="trainFrom">Train from</param>

///<param name="trainTo">Train to</param>

private void TrainNetwork(DateTime trainFrom, DateTime trainTo, TrainingStatus status)

{

if (p_input == null || p_ideal == null)

CreateTrainingSets(trainFrom, trainTo); /*Create training sets, according to input parameters*/

p_trainThread = Thread.CurrentThread; int epoch = 1;

ITrain train = null; try

{

var trainSet = new BasicNeuralDataSet(p_input, p_ideal); train = new ResilientPropagation(p_network, trainSet); double error;

do

{

train.Iteration(); error = train.Error; if (status != null)

status.Invoke(epoch, error, TrainingAlgorithm.Resilient); epoch++;

} while (error > MAX_ERROR);

}

catch (ThreadAbortException) {/*Training aborted*/ p_trainThread = null; }

finally

{

train.FinishTraining();

}

p_trainThread = null;

}

/// Abort training

public void AbortTraining()

{

if (p_trainThread != null) p_trainThread.Abort();

}

///Export neural network

///<param name="path"></param> [System.Security.Permissions.FileIOPermission(System.Security.Permissions.SecurityAction.Demand)] public void ExportNeuralNetwork(string path)

{

if (p_network == null)

throw new NullReferenceException("Network reference is set to null. Nothing to export."); Encog.Util.SerializeObject.Save(path, p_network);

}

///Load neural network

///<param name="path">Path to previously serialized object</param>

public void LoadNeuralNetwork(string path)

{

p_network = (BasicNetwork)Encog.Util.SerializeObject.Load(path); HiddenLayers = p_network.Structure.Layers.Count - 2 /*1 input, 1 output*/; HiddenUnits = p_network.Structure.Layers[1].NeuronCount;

}

///Predict the results

///<returns>List with the prediction results</returns>

public List<PredictionResults> Predict(DateTime predictFrom, DateTime predictTo)

{

List<PredictionResults> results = new List<PredictionResults>();

double[] present = new double[INPUT_TUPLES * INDEXES_TO_CONSIDER]; double[] actualOutput = new double[OUTPUT_SIZE];

int index = 0;

foreach (var sample in p_manager.Samples)

{

if (sample.Date.CompareTo(predictFrom) > 0 && sample.Date.CompareTo(predictTo) < 0)

{

PredictionResults result = new PredictionResults();

p_manager.GetInputData(index - INPUT_TUPLES, present);

p_manager.GetOutputData(index - INPUT_TUPLES, actualOutput); var data = new BasicNeuralData(present);

var predict = p_network.Compute(data);

result.ActualSp = actualOutput[0] * (p_manager.MaxCSVFinance - p_manager.MinCSVFinance) + p_manager.MinCSVFinance;

result.PredictedSp = predict[0] * (p_manager.MaxCSVFinance - p_manager.MinCSVFinance) + p_manager.MinCSVFinance;

result.Date = sample.Date;

ErrorCalculation error = new ErrorCalculation(); error.UpdateError(actualOutput, predict.Data); result.Error = error.CalculateRMS(); results.Add(result);

}

index++;

}

return results;

}
